OL,6,FThe investigation identified three
OL,7,F"benefit factories" in London where
OL,8,Frepeated false claims for benefits
OL,9,Foriginated from.
OL,11,FThe businesses claimed to help people
OL,12,Fget a national insurance number and
OL,13,Fbenefits which they were entitled to.
OL,15,FBut after applicants made their
OL,16,Fbenefits claims through the gang, the
OL,17,Fmoney went into the hands of the
OL,18,Forganised crime group and was
OL,19,Flaundered between bank accounts
OL,20,Fthrough transfers, and withdrawn in
OL,21,Fcash.
